fields.name: New Shepard
fields.description: Showcase the successful launch of the New Shepard rocket.

fields.name: Astrolab Patch
fields.description: A patch made to symbolise the contribution of the European Space Agency to the international space station.

fields.name: Appolo 1
fields.description: One of the worst tragedies in the history of spaceflight occurred on January 27, 1967 when the crew of Gus Grissom, Ed White, and Roger Chaffee were killed in a fire in the Apollo Command Module during a preflight test at Cape Canaveral. This was made commemorate the astronauts

fields.name: Rocket Lab First Patch
fields.description: This patch was made to showcase the first electron rocket. The mission saw Electron complete a perfect first stage burn, stage separation, second stage ignition and fairing separation. Electron successfully reached space and put Rocket Lab in an incredibly strong position to accelerate into commercial operations.

fields.name: Space X Demo 2
fields.description: The Demo-2 mission was the first launch with astronauts of the SpaceX Crew Dragon spacecraft and Falcon 9 rocket to the International Space Station as part of the agency's Commercial Crew Program. The test flight served as an end-to-end demonstration of SpaceX's crew transportation system
